<br>
There is an easy way around the sniping issue and one which I have personally tested and found to be most effective.  Drastic, but effective.<br>
<br>
All guilds which take part in the raid reservation program look out for each other.  You're going to have to start cooperating, lads.  If someone gets sniped then all guilds work together to make the game a living hell for the snipers.  This means the sniping guild will suddenly find all of their normally scheduled raids sniped.  We fight fire with fire.  It's a tactic I used on Vox/Dragon raids and it is most effective.  Not the nicest way to conduct one's gaming experience, admittedly, but it does work.  If your impulse actions to snipe someone will lead to your inability to play the game as you would wish in the future it is a major incentive to Play Nice.<br>
<br>
But this should not need to be the case.  I know people in all of the major guilds and not everyone is childish about major mobs.  Most people are willing to play fair and play nice if given half the chance.  If we actually play the game as it was supposed to be played, helping each other out and watching each other's backs, there is no reason why such a schedule cannot be made a success.<br>
<br>
And the first rule of the reservation system would be that no block bookings are allowed.  So we are all sorry to hear that you are quitting the game next week, Kilamyan.<br>
<br>
Trewayn Fifate<br>
